# Strong Types (mp-units)

All distances and angles use types from `include/drone_mapper/Units.h`.

## Required types

- `PhysicalLength`, `XLength`, `YLength`, `ZLength`, `Position3D`
- `HorizontalAngle`, `AltitudeAngle`, `Orientation`

## Rules

```cpp
// BAD — e16
void move(double distance_cm);
struct TickSnapshot { double x, y; };

// GOOD
types::MovementResult advance(PhysicalLength distance);
```

```cpp
// BAD — e03
double d = length.numerical_value_in(cm);
double x = pos.x.numerical_value_in(cm) + 1.0;

// GOOD — quantity arithmetic
auto next = pos.x + 10.0 * cm;
auto dist = si::sqrt(x * x + y * y);
```

## Boundaries

YAML/`.npy` parsing may read numbers as doubles — convert to strong types **immediately** at the parse boundary.

## Aliases

Import unit symbols via `Units.h` once per file. **No** per-function `namespace su = mp_units::si::unit_symbols` (e17s).
